** Sydney (preferable) OR Melbourne (preferable), Brisbane OR Adelaide **

  * ** Permanent role; hybrid working model; join large BA Community **
  * ** Must have strong technical experience with Protect and min 4 years’ BA exp **
  * ** Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement essential **

We’re never just satisfied with how things are – because we know how things
could be and it’s our expert Technology team who forge ahead every day to make
those ‘what ifs’ a reality.

Welcome to a place where you can chase real progress and drive real change,
and that includes your own career. Being a part of Technology at Suncorp Group
means being switched on, endlessly curious and always adaptable. In return,
you’ll be supported to bring your own ideas to the table and challenge
conventions – with the aim of making life a little brighter, simpler and
better for our customers and each other.

** About the role: **

Suncorp is embarking on one the largest transformation programs we have
undertaken, and we now require Technical Business Analysts who have strong
technical experience working on the Protect system.

You will have at least three years Protect experience, with strong technical
knowledge with the back-end of the Protect system, combined with the ability
to understand the business and liaise confidently with senior stakeholders.

You will have the opportunity to join our large Analysis Chapter that supports
a variety of medium to large scale programs across the Suncorp Group. The
Chapter consists of around 200 like-minded analysts, where ideas and best
practice are shared via masterclasses and knowledge sharing. You will support
projects being delivered in a continuous delivery model (Agile) as well as
initiatives using traditional project delivery models.

Suncorp is proud of our fantastic culture where you will be supported in your
career development.

** **

** What you’ll do: **

  * Leverage your Protect and insurance knowledge to recommend processes, simplify solutions or influence decision making 
  * Understand the screen flows, integration points, data flow 
  * Given the requirements are being built and no “big picture” exists, you will need to be flexible, open and self-motivated to drive the outcome 
  * Work closely with squad / project members, including but not limited to Delivery lead, Scrum Master, Developers, Tech Leads, and Business stakeholders to identify, capture, plan, document and deliver business requirements 
  * Create detailed user stories to support delivery. 
  * Document current and future state processes and identify opportunities for improvement. 
  * Work collaboratively with delivery teams and business stakeholders to validate business requirements and develop recommendations and solutions that meet business and customer needs. 
  * Raise, and support mitigation and resolution of, risks and issues using established tools and frameworks were applicable. 
  * Suncorp offers a hybrid way of working where you will be expected to be in the office approx. 2 days per week. 

** **

** What you’ll bring: **

  * ** ESSENTIAL: ** Minimum 4 years’ technical business analysis experience from a large organisation 
  * ** ESSENTIAL: ** Minimum 3 year’s working with Protect from a Technical viewpoint with the ability to navigate your way around the system 
  * ** ESSENTIAL: ** Previous insurance background and understand the insurance policy lifecycle 
  * Previous experience mentoring and training junior team members with a passion for sharing your knowledge to create a high performing team environment 
  * Minimum 3 years’ Agile, Lean and waterfall experience including knowledge of Agile practices, workshops, and Agile ceremonies facilitation 
  * Must be able to translate and understand business and technical requirements and provide appropriate alternatives and solutions to meet those requirements. 
  * Strong stakeholder engagement, relationship management and influencing skills including experience in dealing with various/senior levels of stakeholders internally and externally. 
  * Strong problem-solving and negotiation skills 
  * Strong team player with a positive attitude, willingness to learn and desire to make a difference 
  * Must be able to manage multiple complex initiatives with competing deadlines, while also working autonomously. 

** What we can offer you: **

  * Discounts and offers on a range of retail favourite stores as well as banking and insurance products. 
  * A range of flexible working and leave options, including 20 weeks paid parental leave, 4 weeks secondary carer leave, and unlimited paid emergency response leave. 
  * Invest in your brighter future with ongoing study support and career development programs. 
  * Give back to our communities with payroll giving, donation matching and paid volunteer leave. 
  * Prioritise your work/life balance with our robust employee assistance program and dedicated employee council. 

** **

